      "content": "Research consistently shows that while minimum wage hikes can reduce employment in small, labor-intensive rural businesses, they often lead to price increases that disproportionately hurt low-income consumers who rely on those local shops. Studies indicate that the \"idealistic theory\" of higher spending frequently gets offset by reduced demand or business closures, leaving the very people the policy aims to help with fewer affordable options in their community. Ultimately, the data suggests that without careful implementation, these hikes can create a net loss of economic activity in areas where small businesses are already struggling to survive.",
